          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Targets used are in a form  of  pure  metal  disk  of",
                " natural isotopes.",
                "                    Mass (g/cm**2):",
                " Al      Cu      Zr      Sn      Ho      Ta      U",
                "8.10    5.40    2.43    2.74    2.60    2.70    1.55",
                "      Pb(0.5mm)   Pb(1mm)   Pb(2mm)    Pb (4 mm)",
                "        0.56        1.13      2.27        4.54"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "STANK"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Spherical  4pi neutron  detector consisted of",
                " 500 l gadolinium loaded liquid  scintillator  viewed",
                " by eight photomultiplier tubes."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The prompt  g-rays  from  thermal  neutron  radiative",
                " capture in  gadolinium  nuclei emitted at differrent",
                " times within a range of roughly  25  microsec  after",
                " neitron emission   were  used  for  photoabsorptoion",
                " cross section determination.",
                "It  was  shown  that  for  energy range 145 - 440 MeV",
                " photoabsorption  cross  section  is equal to partial",
                " reaction (g,2n) cross section."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "HISTORY": [
